Introduction

NU’EST (short for New Establish Style Tempo) was a five-members South Korean boy group formed by Pledis Entertainment. They debuted on March 15, 2012, with the digital single "FACE".

Their fandom name "ㄴㅇㅅㅌ" (also stylized as LOVE or L.O.Λ.E) is derived from the hangul name "뉴이스트". Removing all the vowels which would leave the consonants "ㄴㅇㅅㅌ", resembling the English word "Love".

In 2018, all members except Aaron participated in MNET's survival show Produce 101 Season 2. Although all members did good, only Minhyun was able to debut and promote as a member of the final group WANNA ONE. During that time, the four remaining members promoted as a sub-unit called NU’EST W (W coming from “Waiting”).

On March 1st, 2022 it was announced that the group will officially disband on March 15, 2022 with Aaron, JR and Ren leaving Pledis Entertainment while Baekho and Minhyun renewed their contracts with the agency.

They released one last album titled "Needle & Bubble" on March 15, 2022 and officially disbanded the same day on their 10th year anniversary.
